2025 STATE OF WYOMING 25LSO-0789
HOUSE BILL NO. HB0302
Governmental immunity for use of firearms.
Sponsored by: Representative(s) Connolly, Campbell, K,
Lawley, Posey and Wylie and Senator(s) Boner
and Crago
A BILL
for
1 AN ACT relating to governmental claims; clarifying that
2 governmental entities are not liable for incidents related
3 to the use of firearms; making conforming amendments; and
4 providing for an effective date.
5
6 Be It Enacted by the Legislature of the State of Wyoming:
7
8 Section 1. W.S. 1-39-104 by creating a new subsection
9 (e) and 21-3-132 by creating a new subsection (k) are
10 amended to read:
11
12 1-39-104. Granting immunity from tort liability;
13 liability on contracts; exceptions.
14
1 HB0302

2025 STATE OF WYOMING 25LSO-0789
1 (e) A governmental entity shall be immune from
2 liability for any tort associated with any claim arising
3 solely from or related to a public employee's use, or
4 failure to use, a firearm. For purposes of this subsection,
5 a public employee who is acting within the scope of his
6 duty when using or failing to use a firearm shall be
7 entitled to a defense at the governmental entity's expense
8 in accordance with subsection (b) of this section.
9
10 21-3-132. Possession of firearms on school property.
11
12 (k) Pursuant to W.S. 1-39-104, a school district
13 shall be immune from liability for any tort associated with
14 any claim arising solely from or related to a school
15 district employee's use, or failure to use, a firearm that
16 is carried in accordance with this section.
17
18 Section 2. This act is effective July 1, 2025.
